      <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
         <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
         <p>Illustrator.</p>
         <p>Helen Moore Sewell, the daughter of William Elbridge Sewell and Minnie Moore, was born
            into a Navy family and spent part of her early years in Japan and Guam. She attended the
            Pratt Institute and studied painting with the artist Archipenko. She worked on Christmas
            and greeting cards, and illustrated many books, particularly for children. She was the
            original illustrator for the "Little House" books by Laura Ingalls Wilder. She later
            wrote and illustrated her own books for children.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Correspondence with publishers, other letters, photographs, and original illustrations
            and artwork for her cards and books.</p>
      </scopecontent>
